- "average wave height" is the mean height of waves recorded by the data source;
- "average wind speed" is the mean speed of the wind recorded by the data source.

- 'Average wind speed' is measured in meters per second (m/s);
- 'Average wind direction' is measured in degrees;
- 'Average wave height' is measured in meters (m);
- 'Wind data count' and 'wave data count' refer to the number of data entries for wind and wave, respectively;
- The dataset must have been collected after January 1, 2022, to be considered.

